  "keyFeatures": [
    "Unity-inspired GameObject/Component entity system with MonoBehaviour scripting lifecycle",
    "Multi-backend GPU rendering via Veldrid (OpenGL, Vulkan, DirectX 11, Metal)",
    "PBR (Physically Based Rendering) with HDR, shadows, and post-processing effects",
    "Complete editor with docking windows, asset browser, inspector, scene view, and hierarchy",
    "Double-precision physics via Jitter2 with raycasting and layer collision matrices",
    "Asset pipeline with custom importers, GUID references, meta files, and dependency tracking",
    "Immediate-mode GUI system for both runtime and editor use",
    "Navigation mesh support via DotRecast (Recast & Detour)",
    "Coroutine system and ScriptableObjects matching Unity's API patterns",
    "Cross-platform: Windows, Linux, and macOS",
    "Hot-reload assembly system and undo/redo in the editor",
    "Node graph system for visual scripting foundations",
    "64-bit large world coordinates with camera-relative rendering",
    "OpenAL audio with 3D positional support"
  ],
